4:
Yahweh, be kind to me when you help your people;
\q2 help me when you rescue them.
\q1

6:
We and our ancestors have sinned;
\q2 we have done what is wicked and evil.
\q1

11:
Then their enemies were drowned in the water of the Sea of Reeds;
\q2 not one of them was left.
\q1

13:
But they soon forgot what he had done for them;
\q2 they did things without waiting to find out what Yahweh wanted them to do.
\q1

40:
So Yahweh became very angry with his people;
\q2 he was completely disgusted with them.
\q1
